{"title": "Weird Tales, Volume 1", "description": "These stories form the first volume of the renowned <i>Tales of Hoffman</i>. They are fantasies with hints of the supernatural\u2014quintessential Romanticism. Writers of the Romantic period typically seek to lift the spirit to awe, wonder, love, horror, or other extremes of emotion. Hoffmann is drawn to such experiences, particularly as they relate to the creative process. Although he occasionally arouses them in the reader, he more often examines them critically or, in the case of hysterical excesses, especially infatuation, satirizes them. - Summary by T. A. Copeland", "duration": 43351, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "969", "name": "E. T. A. Hoffmann"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/librivoxcdcoverart36/weirdtales_2004.jpg", "copyright_year": "1885", "genres": ["Literary Fiction", "Romance", "Fantasy Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Thomas A. Copeland"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Thomas A. Copeland"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "BillTurns"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Cremona Violin, Part 1", "readers": [6249], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/weirdtales1_2004_librivox/weirdtales1_01_hoffmann_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2602}, {"section": 2, "title": "The Cremona Violin, Part 2", "readers": [6249], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/weirdtales1_2004_librivox/weirdtales1_02_hoffmann_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1261}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Fermata", "readers": [6249], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/weirdtales1_2004_librivox/weirdtales1_03_hoffmann_64kb.mp3", "duration": 3226}, {"section": 4, "title": "Signor Formica, Part 1", "readers": [6249], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/weirdtales1_2004_librivox/weirdtales1_04_hoffmann_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1973}, {"section": 5, "title": "Signor Formica, Part 2", "readers": [6249], "path": "https://www.archive.o